Description: CUNA agreed to pay $314,000 in penalties along with $270,000 in remediation to resolve multistate allegations that it violated regulations regarding premium refunds.
NASD Regulation, Inc. announced two separate enforcement actions involving sales of variable annuities and the supervision of sales activities.
Notes: FINRA is a securities industry self-regulatory body authorized by the federal government. This case was handled by its predecessor, the National Association of Securities Dealers (NASD).
